cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.CY

The paper discusses the use of machine learning and motion capture sensors for evaluating patient performance in rehabilitation programs. This falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as well as machine learning (cs.LG). The use of motion capture sensors also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) to some extent. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of data representation and feature engineering, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
